review_text: Es un buen lugar para niños de 6 años para abajo pienso
A nice park in South Center City! Enjoy the events they have like live music in the summer.
Nice park. The toddlers had a great time. My first time there and my only frustration was there were no public trash cans.

Sometimes it is simply nice to have a quiet favoured little place to retreat for some personal reflective time and this little park certainly "meets the mark". Nice to stroll in with a little snack, a book or just to sit and chill out, particularly on a warm summers day. Appreciated especially by those who favour a "pet free" environment, which in turn leads to an increased hygiene level. A perfect setting perhaps for older citizens in particular to gather and enjoy long hours of conversation about "the good old days" !

Update:  it's randomly used!  I saw someone teaching children a class out here recently, it was fun to watch and I'm glad the parents have plenty of benches to sit on.

I walk by here frequently, but hardly ever see anyone using this park.  They have some nice benches, good plants and a great grassy area.  No dogs are allowed at all which is a shame and probably why it's never used.
very sad that this is not a dog friendly park. no trash cans either. what a shame.

We revisited this little park and were shocked to see the historic mural was gone, replaced by residential housing. The park does not allow dogs. There's a grassy area, a few plantings and a little free library box. We spotted a bench to sit and relax. This is a walk-to neighborhood park. Street parking available nearby is scarce.
Saw lots of kids playing, and parents watching.

Cozy park with a few benches on the perimeter. It appears well maintained but the lack of large trees would make it a very warm place to enjoy an afternoon.

A great little neighborhood park. It's tiny, but the few benches have nice shade and the large grassy knoll is great for laying out.

Beautiful local park that is kid and dog friendly (on leash only, pack it in pack it out - we are still having great difficulty getting trashcans set up). They just got a major haul of some fresh trees and shrubs to help grow this into a true urban gem. Check it out, and if you get a craving for coffee, there is the amazing Ultimo a block away, and if you're feeling a bit friskier, there is the Sidecar Bar and Grill right across the street with some notoriously amazing burgers and always a great tap selection...added bonus: Sidecar also allows dogs on leash at their outdoor tables!
Great community park!  Good enclosed open space for young kids.  Nice spot for picnic on warm days.  Often live music events in the summer.
